Drama series based on the true story of the Mottershead family who, in the face of staunch opposition and huge personal sacrifice, founded Chester Zoo in the 1930s.

1/6 George attempts to build his dream - a zoo without bars.

2/6 George attempts to rescue two Himalayan black bears from a cave in Matlock.
 
3/6 The family confront a barrage of hostility from the residents of Upton.
 
4/6 The Mottersheads must hastily organise a benefit to raise money after a bear escape. 
 
5/6 George ventures to London for one last attempt to get planning permission. 

6/6 The Mottersheads prepare for the appeal that will decide the fate of the zoo.
